1 AN ACT concerning tobacco products; authorizing the sale of electronic
2 cigarettes in cigarette vending machines; amending K.S.A. 79-3301,
3 79-3303 and 79-3399 and K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 79-3321 and repealing
4 the existing sections.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. K.S.A. 79-3301 is hereby amended to read as follows: 79-
8 3301. As used in K.S.A. 79-3301 et seq., and amendments thereto:
9 (a) "Act" means the Kansas cigarette and tobacco products act.
10 (b) "Carrier" means one who transports cigarettes from a
11 manufacturer to a wholesale dealer or from one wholesale dealer to
12 another.
13 (c) "Carton" means the container used by the manufacturer of
14 cigarettes in which no more than 10 packages of cigarettes are placed prior
15 to shipment from such manufacturer.
16 (d) "Cigarette" means any roll for smoking, made wholly or in part of
17 tobacco, irrespective of size or shape, and irrespective of tobacco being
18 flavored, adulterated or mixed with any other ingredient if the wrapper is
19 in greater part made of any material except tobacco.
20 (e) "Conspicuous location or place" means a location or place
21 available to the general public.
22 (f) "Consumer" means the person purchasing or receiving cigarettes
23 or tobacco products for final use.
24 (g) "Contracting entity" means any public or private person, firm or
25 entity that has entered into a contract with the secretary of revenue to
26 provide services.
27 (h) "Dealer" means any person who engages in the sale or
28 manufacture of cigarettes, tobacco products or electronic cigarettes in the
29 state of Kansas, and who is required to be licensed under the provisions of
30 this act.
31 (i) "Dealer establishment" means any location or premises, other than
32 vending machine locations, at or from which cigarettes, tobacco products
33 or electronic cigarettes are sold, and where records are kept.
34 (j) "Director" means the director of taxation.
35 (k) "Distributor" means:

