1 (1) Any person engaged in the business of selling tobacco products in
2 this state who brings, or causes to be brought, into this state from outside
3 the state any tobacco products for sale;
4 (2) any person who makes, manufactures, fabricates or stores tobacco
5 products in this state for sale in this state; or
6 (3) any person engaged in the business of selling tobacco products
7 outside this state who ships or transports tobacco products to any person in
8 the business of selling tobacco products in this state.
9 (l) "Division" means the division of taxation.
10 (m) "Electronic cigarette" means a battery-powered device, whether
11 or not such device is shaped like a cigarette, that can provide inhaled doses
12 of nicotine by delivering a vaporized solution by means of cartridges or
13 other chemical delivery systems.
14 (n) "Importer" means the same as provided defined in 26 U.S.C. §
15 5702(k).
16 (o) "License" means the privilege of a licensee to sell cigarettes or
17 tobacco products in the state of Kansas, and the written evidence of such
18 authority or privilege as issued by the director.
19 (p) "Licensee" means any person holding a current license issued
20 pursuant to this act.
21 (q) "Manufacturer" means the same as provided defined in 26 U.S.C.
22 § 5702(d).
23 (r) "Manufacturer's salesperson" means a person employed by a
24 cigarette manufacturer who sells cigarettes, manufactured by such
25 employer and procured from wholesale dealers.
26 (s) (1) "Package" means a container in which no more than 25
27 individual cigarettes are wrapped and sealed by the manufacturer of
28 cigarettes prior to shipment to a wholesale dealer;.
29 (2) For the purposes of K.S.A. 79-3321(v) and (w), and amendments
30 thereto, "package" means the same as provided defined in 15 U.S.C. §
31 1332(4).
32 (t) "Person" means any individual, partnership, society, association,
33 joint-stock company, corporation, estate, receiver, trustee, assignee, referee
34 or any other person acting in a fiduciary or representative capacity whether
35 appointed by a court or otherwise and any combination of individuals.
36 (u) "Received" means the coming to rest of cigarettes for sale by any
37 dealer in the state of Kansas.
38 (v) "Retail dealer" or "retailers" means a person, other than a vending
39 machine operator, in possession of cigarettes or electronic cigarettes for
40 the purpose of sale to a consumer.
41 (w) "Sale" means any transfer of title or possession or both,
42 exchange, barter, distribution or gift of cigarettes, tobacco products or
43 electronic cigarettes, with or without consideration.

