1 (x) "Sample" means cigarettes or tobacco products distributed to
2 members of the general public at no cost for purposes of promoting the
3 product.
4 (y) "Self-service display" means a display that contains cigarettes or
5 tobacco products and is located in an area openly accessible to a retail
6 dealer's consumers, and from which such consumers can readily access
7 cigarettes or tobacco products without the assistance of a salesperson, and
8 which is knowingly utilized by the retail dealer to market and sell
9 cigarettes and tobacco products to consumers. A display case that holds
10 cigarettes or tobacco products behind locked doors does not constitute a
11 self-service display.
12 (z) "Stamps" means tax indicia applied by means of heat process,
13 pressure or any other process approved by the director.
14 (aa) "Tax indicia" means visible evidence of tax payment in the form
15 of stamps.
16 (bb) "Tobacco products" means cigars, cheroots, stogies, periques;
17 granulated, plug cut, crimp cut, ready rubbed and other smoking tobacco;
18 snuff, snuff flour; cavendish; plug and twist tobacco; fine cut and other
19 chewing tobaccos; shorts; refuse scraps, clippings, cuttings and sweepings
20 of tobacco, and other kinds and forms of tobacco, prepared in such manner
21 as to be suitable for chewing or smoking in a pipe or otherwise, or both for
22 chewing and smoking. Tobacco products do not include cigarettes.
23 (cc) "Tobacco specialty store" means a dealer establishment that
24 derives at least 65% of such dealer establishment's revenue from cigarettes
25 or tobacco products.
26 (dd) "Vending machine" means any coin operated machine,
27 contrivance or device, by means of which merchandise may be sold.
28 (ee) "Vending machine distributor" means any person who sells
29 cigarette or electronic cigarette vending machines to a vending machine
30 operator operating vending machines in the state of Kansas.
31 (ff) (1) "Vending machine operator" means any person who places a
32 vending machine, owned, leased or operated by such person, at locations
33 where cigarettes or electronic cigarettes are sold from such vending
34 machine.
35 (2) The owner or lessee of the premises upon which a vending
36 machine is placed shall not be considered the operator of the machine, nor
37 shall the owner or lessee, or any employee or agent of the owner or lessee
38 be considered an authorized agent of the vending machine operator, if the
39 owner or lessee does not own or lease the machine and the owner's or
40 lessee's sole remuneration from the machine is a flat rental fee or
41 commission based upon the number or value of cigarettes or electronic
42 cigarettes sold from the machine, or a combination of both.
43 (gg) "Wholesale dealer" means any person who sells cigarettes or

