10 Sec. 4. K.S.A. 79-3399 is hereby amended to read as follows: 79-
11 3399. (a) On and after July 1, 2017, A tax is hereby imposed upon the
12 privilege of selling or dealing in electronic cigarettes in this state by any
13 person engaged in business as a distributor thereof, at the rate of $.05 per
14 milliliter of consumable material for electronic cigarettes and a
15 proportionate tax at the like rate on all fractional parts thereof. For
16 electronic cigarettes in the possession of retail dealers or vending machine
17 operators for which tax has not been paid, tax shall be imposed under this
18 subsection at the earliest time the retail dealer or vending machine
19 operator:
20 (1) Brings or causes to be brought into this state from without the
21 state electronic cigarettes for sale;
22 (2) makes, manufactures or fabricates electronic cigarettes in this
23 state for sale in this state; or
24 (3) sells electronic cigarettes to consumers within this state.
25 (b) As used in this section, "consumable material" means any liquid
26 solution or other material that is depleted as an electronic cigarette is used.
27 (c) The secretary of revenue shall adopt rules and regulations to
28 implement the provisions of this section.
29 Sec. 5. K.S.A. 79-3301, 79-3303 and 79-3399 and K.S.A. 2024 Supp.
30 79-3321 are hereby repealed.
31 Sec. 6. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
32 publication in the statute book.

